# 1. Global defaults
# Automatically detect text files and normalize them to LF in the repo.
* text=auto

# 2. Genesis Artifacts - The "Deep Freeze"
# We treat the entire directory as binary to ensure bit-for-bit integrity.
# This covers .md, .json, .log and any other files inside.
# Note: Some examples (may) need integrity to work as example for integrity proof
genesis_artifacts/** binary

# N.B. -text may exclude specific text files from being treated as text.
# -text would ensure, sha256sum will always give the same result.
# to keep the files diff-able but stop normalization:
# specific_file.md -text
# In our case, lets use binary, it is even more safe.


# 3. Standard JSON Handling
# Ensure JSON files are normalized but remain diffable in the rest of the project.
*.json text

# 4. Standard Log Handling
# Usually logs are gitignored, but if tracked, treat as text.
*.log text

# 5. Python source files
# Ensure they are handled as text for clean cross-platform collaboration.
*.py text

# 6. Documentation (outside of genesis_artifacts)
*.md text

# 5. Shell scripts
# Force LF so they remain executable on Linux/Unix systems.
*.sh text eol=lf

# 6. Actual binary files
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.pdf binary
*.pyc binary